{
  "notes": "Adversarial probes for left/right/mid/trim/ljust/rjust (non-numeric args, arg-count/type errors, LBUF boundary). Found and fixed two real bugs here: (1) FunctionRegistry\u0027s generic arg-count-error wording used \u0027BETWEEN N AND M ARGUMENTS\u0027 unconditionally, but a two-value range (e.g. ljust/rjust\u0027s 2-3) actually reads \u0027N OR M ARGUMENTS\u0027 -- only wider ranges (trim\u0027s 1-3) use \u0027BETWEEN\u0027. (2) mid() was missing the LBUF_SIZE-1 (7999) upper-bound check on start/len that functions.c enforces (mid(hello,8000,2) -\u003e #-1 OUT OF RANGE). One documented, accepted divergence intentionally NOT included here: mid(hello,99999999999999999999,2) -- a start/len literal that overflows a 64-bit long doesn\u0027t trip the LBUF check the way C\u0027s own (implementation-defined) overflow behavior does, since Value.atoi() collapses unparseable-as-long input to 0 rather than replicating C\u0027s overflow value; see StringFunctions.mid\u0027s javadoc.",
  "cases": [
    {
      "input": "left(hello,abc)",
      "expected": ""
    },
    {
      "input": "left(hello,3abc)",
      "expected": "hel"
    },
    {
      "input": "left(hello, )",
      "expected": ""
    },
    {
      "input": "left(hello,1e10)",
      "expected": "h"
    },
    {
      "input": "right(hello,abc)",
      "expected": ""
    },
    {
      "input": "right(hello,1.5)",
      "expected": "o"
    },
    {
      "input": "mid(hello,abc,2)",
      "expected": "he"
    },
    {
      "input": "mid(hello,2,abc)",
      "expected": ""
    },
    {
      "input": "mid(hello,-abc,2)",
      "expected": "he"
    },
    {
      "input": "mid(hello,1.5,2)",
      "expected": "el"
    },
    {
      "input": "left(hello,99999999999999999999)",
      "expected": ""
    },
    {
      "input": "mid(hello,-99999999999999999999,2)",
      "expected": "he"
    },
    {
      "input": "mid(hello,8000,2)",
      "expected": "#-1 OUT OF RANGE"
    },
    {
      "input": "mid(hello,7999,2)",
      "expected": ""
    },
    {
      "input": "mid(hello,100,-99999999999999999999)",
      "expected": ""
    },
    {
      "input": "ljust(hi,abc)",
      "expected": "hi"
    },
    {
      "input": "ljust(hi,5,)",
      "expected": "hi   "
    },
    {
      "input": "rjust(hi,-5)",
      "expected": "hi"
    },
    {
      "input": "trim(hello,x,yz)",
      "expected": "#-1 SEPARATOR MUST BE ONE CHARACTER"
    },
    {
      "input": "trim(hello,,x)",
      "expected": "hello"
    },
    {
      "input": "trim(hello,L,h)",
      "expected": "ello"
    },
    {
      "input": "trim(hello,R,o)",
      "expected": "hell"
    },
    {
      "input": "trim()",
      "expected": ""
    },
    {
      "input": "ljust(hi)",
      "expected": "#-1 FUNCTION (LJUST) EXPECTS 2 OR 3 ARGUMENTS"
    },
    {
      "input": "ljust(hi,5,x,extra)",
      "expected": "#-1 FUNCTION (LJUST) EXPECTS 2 OR 3 ARGUMENTS"
    },
    {
      "input": "left(hello,add(1,2))",
      "expected": "hel"
    },
    {
      "input": "mid(,1,2)",
      "expected": ""
    },
    {
      "input": "trim(a,b,c,d)",
      "expected": "#-1 FUNCTION (TRIM) EXPECTS BETWEEN 1 AND 3 ARGUMENTS"
    },
    {
      "input": "rjust(hi)",
      "expected": "#-1 FUNCTION (RJUST) EXPECTS 2 OR 3 ARGUMENTS"
    },
    {
      "input": "rjust(hi,5,x,extra)",
      "expected": "#-1 FUNCTION (RJUST) EXPECTS 2 OR 3 ARGUMENTS"
    },
    {
      "input": "trim(a,b,c)",
      "expected": "a"
    },
    {
      "input": "trim(a,b)",
      "expected": "a"
    }
  ]
}
